# Lingui Localization Guidelines

Use @lingui for all text content in the app. Support English and Spanish initially.

## Text Content

- Use Trans component for JSX text content
- Use t macro for string values and placeholders
- Import from @lingui/macro for compile-time optimizations
- Use useLingui hook to access i18n instance

## Best Practices

- Wrap ALL user-facing text with Trans or t
- Never hardcode strings - always use lingui
- Use meaningful IDs for complex translations
- Include context comments for translators
- Use plurals for count-based messages
- Use variables for dynamic content
- Support ICU message format

## Common Translations

- Menu categories and item names
- Store information and hours
- Navigation labels
- Button text and actions
- Error messages and alerts
- Placeholder text

## File Organization

- Keep translations in locales/ directory
- Use lingui extract to generate message catalogs
- Compile translations before building
